<p><em>Photo by Nathan De Fortunato on Unsplash</em></p>

<p>Open <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminal_(macOS)">Terminal</a> and type the following command:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>defaults write com.apple.screencapture location ~/Documents/Screenshots
killall SystemUIServer
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can customise the directory that you want to save screenshots to. It doesn’t
have to be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">~/Documents/Screenshots</code> if you would prefer another location you
adjust the code above to your preferred folder.</p>

<p>To revert back to saving screenshots to your desktop, type the
following into the terminal window:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>defaults write com.apple.screencapture location ~/Desktop
killall SystemUIServer
</code></pre></div></div>
